Hajib:	哈吉布:
the dark black sky	漆黑的夜空
Hajib	哈吉布
the eunuch guard	太監衛兵
the sleeping eunuch	熟睡的太監
The eunuch seems to be sleeping soundly.	這名太監似乎睡得很沉。
the fountain water	噴泉的水
The sound of the water is almost hypnotic.	水聲幾乎讓人陶醉。
The water at the base of the fountain looks cool and refreshing.	噴泉底部的水看起來清涼宜人。
The torch flickers calmly.	火把靜靜地搖曳著。
the Raseirian Rubber Plant	拉希爾橡膠樹
The Raserian Rubber Plant gets good light and air at the door.	這株拉希爾橡膠樹在門邊能曬到充足陽光與空氣。
the woven carpet	織花地毯
The carpet is finely woven of the best Shapeirian wool.	這張地毯以最上等的夏皮爾羊毛精心織成。
The table is made of hand rubbed Iblia wood from the hills of the Forbidden City of Iblis.	這張桌子是用伊布利斯禁城山丘出產的伊布利亞木材手工打磨而成。
the fountain	噴泉
The world famous Spitting Fish is the pride of Raseir.	這條世界知名的吐水魚是拉希爾的驕傲。
the clay pots	陶罐
The large earthen pots probably contain water.	這些大陶罐裡大概裝著水。
the eunuchs' wine	太監們的酒
It's a fine port, a favorite of the eunuchs, no doubt.	這是一瓶上等波特酒,無疑是太監們的最愛。
the pillows	枕頭
the torch sconce	火把架
The sconce holds the torch.	火把架上架著火把。
the flowers	花朵
A "Friendship Bouquet" brightens any day.	一束「友誼花束」能點亮任何一天。
the doorway to the ancient city	通往古城的門道
the fallen tower	倒塌的高塔
the pale moon	蒼白的月亮
the remains of the ancient city	古城的遺跡
The ancient city, long before it was sealed, bustled with intelligence and magic under these granite cliffs.	早在被封印之前,這座古城曾在這些花崗岩峭壁下,充滿智慧與魔法而繁盛一時。
the entrance to the Forbidden City	禁城的入口
Jutting from the ground like the prow of an ancient shipwreck is the entrance to the Forbidden City.	禁城的入口如古沉船船首般,自地面聳立而出。
the flaming geyser	火焰間歇泉
The flaming geysers seem to spout at predictable intervals.	這些火焰間歇泉似乎會按可預測的間隔噴發。
lava flow	熔岩流
The molten lava gives off an intermittent glow and abundant heat.	熔岩發出斷續的光芒與充沛的熱氣。
You have fallen just off screen to the jagged rocks below.	你墜落到畫面外,摔向下方嶙峋的岩石。
Yeeeooooow!	呀啊啊啊啊啊!
The swift current overwhelms you with emotions as it sweeps you off your feet and carries you away with it.	湍急的水流以排山倒海之勢將你捲倒,並把你一併沖走。
the log	圓木
The old logs and other debris come from above.  The rushing water carries them deep into the caverns far below.	這些老舊圓木與其他殘骸從上方漂來,湍急的水流將它們沖向遠處深邃的洞穴。
the rocks	岩石
the wind	風
The lower cascade falls seemingly forever to the rocks below.	下方的瀑布彷彿永無止盡地傾瀉在岩石上。
the steps	階梯
the waterfall	瀑布
the door to the outside	通往外面的門
